org.openimaj.image.model.pixel

Class HistogramPixelModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.image.model.pixel.PixelClassificationModel<Float[],MBFImage>
      • org.openimaj.image.model.pixel.MBFPixelClassificationModel
        • org.openimaj.image.model.pixel.HistogramPixelModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, ImageClassificationModel<MBFImage>, EstimatableModel<MBFImage,FImage>, Model<MBFImage,FImage>

    public class HistogramPixelModel
extends MBFPixelClassificationModel
    An MBFPixelClassificationModel that classifies an individual pixel by comparing it to a joint (colour) histogram. The histogram is learnt from the positive pixel samples given in training. The probability returned by the classification is determined from the value of the histogram bin in which the pixel being classified falls.
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
